nextObjectMetadata

public ObjectReader nextObjectMetadata()
                                throws IOException
Description copied from interface: ObjectReader
Will read nexts object metadata. You can call this method as many times as you want, with the condition that you use only ObjectReader.metadata(String) method. For example if you call ObjectReader.beginObject() you wont be able to do it anymore (however you still can retrieve the metadata!).

next

public ValueType next()
               throws IOException
Description copied from interface: ObjectReader
If we are in a object it will read the next name/value pair and if we are in an array it will read the next value (except if value is of complex type, in that case after the call to next() you must use one of beginXXX methods).
